# Append-only learning logs written by AI assistants (Bolt / Sentinel / Jules).
# Multiple PRs frequently append entries to the same file at the same time,
# which produces add/add conflicts at the end of file. The `union` merge
# driver tells git to keep both sides' new lines instead of marking them as
# a conflict, which is exactly the behaviour we want for these append-only
# notes. Order is not guaranteed; re-sort by date manually if needed.
#
# Reference: gitattributes(5), section "Merging files".
.jules/**.md merge=union
